      "summary": "Wireguard module exposes rebindable package-level function variables, creating fragile cross-module coupling and hidden runtime behavior changes.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/config/wireguard.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Global assignments `confForWG = Conf`, `getVersionChannelForWG = GetVersionChannel`, `wgKeyGenForCycle = WgKeyGen`, `updateConfTypedForCycle = UpdateConfTyped` in var block.",
        "`UpdateWGConf` and `CycleWgKey` execute through these variables instead of direct function calls, making behavior replaceable via external mutation."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Remove mutable global indirection by calling concrete package functions directly in production and passing dependencies explicitly in exported entrypoints (or constructor) for test seams; if tests require override, use local test-only hooks instead of module-wide mutable variables.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "mutable-package-seams"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "action-contract-silo",
      "summary": "Upload action contracts are represented across modules via parallel string-based types, allowing protocol drift without compiler errors.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "protocol/actions.go centralizes action constants and parser for upload/c2c (`ActionUploadOpenEndpoint`, `ActionUploadReset`, `ParseAction`, `SupportedActions`).",
        "uploadsvc adapter test uses `uploadsvc.ActionOpenEndpoint` and compares/assigns string payload fields (`Action: string(uploadsvc.ActionOpenEndpoint)`), indicating runtime string coupling at module boundaries.",
        "The adapter tests validate payload mapping and unsupported action behavior against `uploadsvc.UnsupportedActionError`, not directly against `protocol/actions` validation contract."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single source of action contract (shared type/enum and parser) in the protocol layer and make uploadsvc consume it directly (or enforce adapter-level validation against that shared contract), removing duplicate action typing and string-based conversion across modules.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "action-contract-silo"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Mutable global seams in production modules blur module boundaries and create hidden side-effect surfaces.",
      "Protocol/action semantics are maintained in parallel representations across packages, making boundaries weak and drift-prone."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "wg-mutable-seams",
      "action-contract-silo"
    ],
